c="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F50%2F01%2Fe9e48286483da3434276533a9b56%2Fgettyimages-2207570274.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F50%2F01%2Fe9e48286483da3434276533a9b56%2Fgettyimages-2207570274.jpg" class="img" alt="Ledisi attends the 2025 Billboard Women in Music at YouTube Theater on March 29 in Inglewood, California." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Ledisi attends the 2025 Billboard Women in Music at YouTube Theater on March 29 in Inglewood, California.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Amy Sussman/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;R&amp;B singer Ledisi is about to embark on her tour for her 14th album, &lt;em&gt;The Crown&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;em&gt; Morning Edition&lt;/em&gt; host Michel Martin told the singer during an interview that she noticed that the body of her music is upbeat, when a lot of popular music is sad. Ledisi said that heading into this year, she wanted everything to feel good. "I still talked about the complexities of life and love and letting go of love, but still always ending on the idea of hope," Ledisi said to Martin. Listen to &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5366046:nx-s1-5437164-1" target="_blank"&gt;snippets of music&lt;/a&gt; from Ledisi's latest album.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Life advice&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-63291" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4000;         --source-height: 2250;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/400/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/900/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/1200/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/1600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/1800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/png" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/1100/quality/50/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+475/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2Faf%2F7db022b343d190d32820e2113b86%2Ffinal-deliverable-edited.png" class="img" alt="Illustration that shows a large pie chart divided into different sections. From the sections, lines connect the slices to various pop-up boxes that depict things people spend money on, like groceries, medication, bills, and stocks. A hand holding a pencil hovers over the pie chart, re-drawing the slices to adapt to economic uncertainty due to tariffs. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 When the economy is hard to predict, tried-and-true financial advice will serve you well, says Lauryn Williams, a certified financial planner and founder of Worth Winning.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Wenjing Yang for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Amid stock market volatility and concerns about rising prices, you might be anxious about your finances. When the economy feels unpredictable, relying on established financial advice can be beneficial. Lauryn Williams, certified financial planner and founder of Worth Winning, explains &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/30/nx-s1-5371631/anxious-about-your-money-right-now-financial-advice-in-times-of-economic-uncertainty" target="_blank"&gt;how to navigate these tricky times&lt;/a&gt; to NPR's&lt;em&gt; Life Kit&lt;/em&gt;. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 Stick to buying the necessities and consider waiting to purchase large, unnecessary items. Exercise restraint instead of stockpiling items.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 Beware of scams, which tend to ramp up around financial crises. Avoid people who pressure you to take quick action.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 Educate yourself about what is happening, but don't let the news, social media, or group chats on the economy incite fear.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 If possible, continue building up your emergency fund and short-term savings. If the economy goes down, you will need something to help you through the hard times.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For more guidance on how to prepare for economic uncertainty, &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5371631:g-s1-63616" target="_blank"&gt;listen to this episode of NPR's&lt;i&gt; Life Kit&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Subscribe to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/life-kit" target="_blank"&gt;the&lt;i&gt; Life Kit&lt;/i&gt; newsletter&lt;/a&gt; for expert advice on love, money, relationships and more.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-64222" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 7935;         --source-height: 4463;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7935x4463+0+413/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2Ff7%2F3a7ae10742979c21884b9f4d184e%2Fap25123849078192.jpg" class="img" alt="Sovereignty, ridden by Junior Alvarado, left, crosses the finish line to win the 151st running of the Kentucky Derby horse race followed by Journalism, ridden by Umberto Rispoli, at Churchill Downs on Saturday, May 3, 2025, in Louisville, Ky." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Sovereignty, ridden by Junior Alvarado, left, crosses the finish line to win the 151st running of the Kentucky Derby horse race followed by Journalism, ridden by Umberto Rispoli, at Churchill Downs on Saturday, May 3, 2025, in Louisville, Ky.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Abbie Parr/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sovereignty &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/05/03/nx-s1-5385847/sovereignty-winner-kentucky-derby-journalism" target="_blank"&gt;won the Kentucky Derby&lt;/a&gt; on a rain-soaked track on Saturday, beating out Journalism, the favorite to win the race.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Faces of Gun Violence exhibit at the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives headquarters &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/05/04/nx-s1-5386668/atf-trump-administration-gun-violence-memorial" target="_blank"&gt;has been taken down&lt;/a&gt;. It showed portraits of 120 people killed by gun violence in the U.S.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Brazilian police say they &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/05/04/nx-s1-5386457/lady-gaga-copacabana-beach-brazil-free-concert" target="_blank"&gt;prevented a planned bomb attack&lt;/a&gt; that was targeting Lady Gaga's free concert in Rio de Janeiro Saturday night. More than 2 million people attended.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
