      <title>Republicans aim to pass Trump's big bill. And, Steve Bannon analyzes Trump's strategy</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2025/04/30/g-s1-63502/up-first-newsletter-trump-100-days-steve-bannon</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2025/04/30/g-s1-63502/up-first-newsletter-trump-100-days-steve-bannon</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/04/30/g-s1-63502/up-first-newsletter-trump-100-days-steve-bannon</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 30 Apr 2025 11:20:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;President Trump marked the 100th day of his second term with a rally in Michigan last night. &lt;/strong&gt;There, Trump cited an editorial alleging that his presidency has been the most consequential in history. Trump has pushed the limits of presidential power, used wartime authorities to crack down on immigration, punished his political enemies and launched a trade war that has upended global relationships. During his hour-and-a-half rally, he &lt;a href="http://www.npr.org/2025/04/29/nx-s1-5380216/trump-100-days-michigan-rally" target="_blank"&gt;falsely claimed to have won&lt;/a&gt; the 2020 presidential election, blamed former President Joe Biden for various national problems, and insisted he's not getting enough credit for his accomplishments.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-63435-1" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6000;         --source-height: 4045;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4045+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F1a%2F15fcf95f485e823ae1feecca3684%2Fgettyimages-2212645692.jpg" class="img" alt="President Trump speaks during a rally at Macomb Community College on in Warren, Mich., on Tuesday to mark his first 100 days in office." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 President Trump speaks during a rally at Macomb Community College on in Warren, Mich., on Tuesday to mark his first 100 days in office.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Scott Olson/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;The key difference between Trump's first and second terms in office so far is that now, he has more experience&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Tamara Keith tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt;. During his first term, he received pushback from his administration. This time, the president has filled his administration with more loyalists. Keith said that at the rally, Trump seemed to be &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1248091514:1269230539" target="_blank"&gt;transitioning to a campaign-style&lt;/a&gt; push for what he calls his "one big beautiful bill," — a massive tax and spending cut measure he is pushing Republicans to pass quickly in Congress.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trump's bill is the main focus for Republicans in Congress as they return to the nation's capital after a two-week recess.&lt;/strong&gt; The House says the goal is to pass the bill by Memorial Day. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;This is an entirely partisan process, because the Democrats, who are unanimously opposed to the bill&lt;/strong&gt;, do not have the power to stop it, NPR's Elena Moore says. Some of the bill is divisive among Republicans. With a razor-thin majority, &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1248091514:1269230539" target="_blank"&gt;virtually full party support&lt;/a&gt; is needed to get this bill across the finish line.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trump's sometime adviser Steve Bannon said he is expecting a "summer like no other,"&lt;/strong&gt; during an interview with &lt;em&gt;Morning Edition&lt;/em&gt; host Steve Inskeep. Bannon promoted Trump's agenda in 2016 and worked in the White House for some time. Political observers keep an eye on Bannon to gauge where Trump's coalition may be going. Watch the video of Bannon and Inskeep's expansive conversation, which included discussions about &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/30/nx-s1-5377567/steve-bannon-praises-trumps-strategy-wants-doges-receipts" target="_blank"&gt;tariffs, immigration and how Trump&lt;/a&gt; is using his power. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧&lt;strong&gt; Bannon expressed to Inskeep that he wants to see more intense attacks on&lt;/strong&gt; universities, both public and private, from the administration — even as many Americans tell pollsters they believe Trump has gone too far. He also wants all Chinese students to be sent home. Bannon says he &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1248091514:1269230539" target="_blank"&gt;wants to see high-value-added manufacturing&lt;/a&gt; return to provide an opportunity for an individual to have a job and support their family while one spouse stays home if they want to. "Once we're back to that, the country is going to be vibrant and robust again," he says.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Living better&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-63046" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5000;         --source-height: 4000;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x4000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4b%2Fc2%2Fac36c9904cf5968e0dab2219515f%2Fnpr-fa.jpg" class="img" alt="NPR_FA.jpg" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Living Better is a &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/series/1176326550/living-better" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;i&gt;special series&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; about what it takes to stay healthy in America.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Many people are currently feeling financial anxiety, brought on by the tens of thousands of federal workers cut from their jobs, the possibility of a recession and other recent developments in the headlines. Some people may experience financial setbacks as a disaster that can trigger intense stress, which can then spiral into serious health problems, like depression, substance abuse, high blood pressure and heart problems. Research shows that how you approach financial stress can be &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/28/nx-s1-5373993/financial-stress-job-loss-mental-health" target="_blank"&gt;key to protecting your health&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;💰 Acknowledging and processing the grief of a job loss is an important step toward moving on and embracing your new financial reality.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💰 Find new ways to utilize your skills with side hustles or volunteering. It can provide purpose and a path forward, and allow you to reinvent yourself.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💰 Give yourself permission not to worry about the future and focus on the immediate present. Carve out a discrete period, like one or three months, to set goals around financial savings and the number of jobs you plan to apply for.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-62588" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6000;         --source-height: 4000;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x4000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2Fdc%2Fad50bce142cc9f61f083351ef598%2Flannaapisukh-npr-bodegacats-1245.jpg 900w, https://npr.brigh