bodega kitten playing with a Lotto ticket at Grand Organic in Brooklyn, New York on March 31, 2025.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Lanna Apisukh for NPR/Lanna Apisukh                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In New York, bodega cats are more than just cute companions for the workers and shoppers at the convenience stores. They contribute to the work by taking care of rodents and attracting customers. However, the felines are illegal in New York City because bodegas sell food. Now, kitty lovers have petitioned to reclassify them as working animals. Check out these &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/24/nx-s1-5339780/bodega-cats" target="_blank"&gt;photos of the cats hard at work&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-63385" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1000;         --source-height: 565;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1000x565+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F09%2Fbb%2F299b5442406fb5a282b4bde66aff%2Fidaho-hagerman-valley-1-copy-1-1000x565.jpg" class="img" alt="In 2024, the Idaho Humanities Council funded a rural historical society’s project to compile 400 biographies of local veterans." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 In 2024, the Idaho Humanities Council funded a rural historical society's project to compile 400 biographies of local veterans.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Hagerman Valley Historical Museum and Idaho Humanities                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Mellon Foundation has announced $15 million in "emergency funding" for state humanities councils across the U.S. The support comes after the government recently &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/29/nx-s1-5381381/mellon-foundation-emergency-funding-humanities-councils-doge" target="_blank"&gt;eliminated $65 million in grants&lt;/a&gt;, affecting museums, historical sites and more.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Trump administration wants to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2025/04/28/nx-s1-5375847/federal-government-may-cut-988-suicide-hotline-for-lgbtq-youth" target="_blank"&gt;reduce funding for specialized services&lt;/a&gt; for LGBTQ+ youth on the 988 Suicide and Crisis Lifeline, based on a leaked budget proposal reviewed by NPR.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The 6888th Central Postal Directory Battalion, the only female unit to serve overseas in World War II, was &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/29/nx-s1-5380784/six-triple-eight-congressional-gold-medal" target="_blank"&gt;honored with a Congressional Gold Medal&lt;/a&gt; yesterday, exactly 80 years after achieving the organizational feat.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
