tspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0f%2F5e%2Ffda28bf04764bd8a72ff84cd8e4b%2Frecording-session-abrami-c-hauskonzerte-6.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0f%2F5e%2Ffda28bf04764bd8a72ff84cd8e4b%2Frecording-session-abrami-c-hauskonzerte-6.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0f%2F5e%2Ffda28bf04764bd8a72ff84cd8e4b%2Frecording-session-abrami-c-hauskonzerte-6.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0f%2F5e%2Ffda28bf04764bd8a72ff84cd8e4b%2Frecording-session-abrami-c-hauskonzerte-6.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0f%2F5e%2Ffda28bf04764bd8a72ff84cd8e4b%2Frecording-session-abrami-c-hauskonzerte-6.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3840x2160+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0f%2F5e%2Ffda28bf04764bd8a72ff84cd8e4b%2Frecording-session-abrami-c-hauskonzerte-6.jpg" class="img" alt="Violinist Esther Abrami realized when she was 25 that none of the hundreds of pieces she had played were composed by women. The results of her journey to change that are on her new album, Women." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Violinist Esther Abrami realized when she was 25 that none of the hundreds of pieces she had played were composed by women. The results of her journey to change that are on her new album, Women.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Hauskonzerte                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Violinist Esther Abrami's new album,&lt;em&gt; Women&lt;/em&gt;, features music by female composers, spotlighting many names that are not often as recognized as their male counterparts. Abrami said that when she came out of university, it hit her that within all those years, none of the hundreds of pieces she learned had been written by women. This acknowledgement sparked her journey and research, which she says "was like opening the door of, like, a hidden treasure." Her album features the world-premiere studio recording of Irish composer Ina Boyle's Violin Concerto. The music also uncovers what women have to say from the Middle Ages to today, dipping into Brazilian dances and pop. Listen to &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5286308:nx-s1-5423381-1" target="_blank"&gt;snippets from the album&lt;/a&gt; and read the story &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/28/nx-s1-5286308/violinist-esther-abrami-female-composers-new-album" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-63110" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4200;         --source-height: 2363;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4200x2363+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faf%2F99%2F6c7433eb44dc965114554cea07f3%2Fbiscuits-and-banjos-npr-cw-55.jpg" class="img" alt="Durham, N.C. - April 26th, 2025: Attendees watch and dance as New Dangerfield performs during the Biscuit and Banjos festival. (Cornell Watson for NPR)" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Durham, N.C. - April 26th, 2025: Attendees watch and dance as New Dangerfield performs during the Biscuit and Banjos festival. (Cornell Watson for NPR)                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Cornell Watson for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Biscuits &amp; Banjos is a new music festival dedicated to reclaiming and exploring Black music. The festival, curated by Grammy-winning artist Rhiannon Giddens, took place this past weekend in Durham, N.C., and featured artists like Taj Mahal, Infinity Song and a Carolina Chocolate Drops reunion. The event also incorporated Durham's Black history with a walking tour of Black Wall Street, panel discussions, square and line dancing, and a juke joint-themed party. Durham-based photojournalist Cornell Watson &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/04/29/nx-s1-5379904/biscuits-and-banjos-music-festival-photos" target="_blank"&gt;photographed the festival&lt;/a&gt; and shared his experience.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-63093" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 7700;         --source-height: 4331;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7700x4331+100+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F87%2F8e971ee641edb90a6ae5f5c87a4d%2Fap22151696379591.jpg" class="img" alt="A transfer truck arrives at a DHL facility in Ludwigsfelde near Berlin, Germany, in May 2022. The company said this week it would resume shipping packages over $800 to individual U.S. customers." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A transfer truck arrives at a DHL facility in Ludwigsfelde near Berlin, Germany, in May 2022. The company said this week it would resume shipping packages over $800 to individual U.S. customers.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Michael Sohn/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The global shipping company DHL has &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/28/nx-s1-5379560/dhl-global-shipments-resume" target="_blank"&gt;resumed shipping packages over&lt;/a&gt; $800 in value to people in the U.S. The reversal comes one week after it said it was halting such shipments due to new U.S. customs regulations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The TAKE IT DOWN Act is now headed to Trump's desk. The bill, which first lady Melania Trump backs, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/28/nx-s1-5380236/take-it-down-act-melania-trump" target="_blank"&gt;aims to implement strict penalties&lt;/a&gt; and guidelines for those who publish and promote revenge porn.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The 2025 NEA Jazz Masters Tribute Concert &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/28/nx-s1-5379977/2025-jazz-masters-kennedy-center-concert" target="_blank"&gt;celebrated its inductees&lt;/a&gt; on Saturday at the Kennedy Center. A prevailing theme throughout the event was jazz's foundation in freedom and its push to transcendence.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
